REAWAKENING OF HINDUISM ON A NATIONAL BASIS (Prabuddha Bharata, September, 1898)
In an interview which a representative of Prabuddha Bharata had recently with the Swami Vivekananda, that great Teacher was asked: &ldquo;What do you consider the distinguishing feature of your movement, Swamiji?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Aggression,&rdquo; said the Swami promptly, &ldquo;aggression in a religious sense only. Other sects and parties have carried spirituality all over India, but since the days of Buddha we have been the first to break bounds and try to flood the world with missionary zeal.
